      static Pattern NAMESPACE_ID_PATTERN
      "A diversicon ID should look something like \'wn31_blabla\', with the first part being a prefix (i.e. \'wn31\'), followed by an underscore \'_\'. More technically, it should be an XML NCName with the further restriction of having a prefix followed by an underscore and a word beginning with a unicode letter. The rest of the word may contain unicode letters, dots \'.\', dashes \'-\', underscores \'_\', but no spaces."

      • fetchH2Db

        public static de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.transform.DBConfig fetchH2Db(File cacheRoot,
                                                  String id,
                                                  String version)
        Restores a packaged H2 db to file system , in a subdirectory of cacheRoot as specified by getCachedDir(File, String, String).

        The database is intended to be accessed in read-only mode

        If already present in cache root: no fetch is performed.
        If not present in cache root: db is first searched in the classpath, if not found is fetched from Github, at correct revision.

        Parameters:
        id - the worldwide unique identifier for the resource, in a format like DivWn31.NAME
        version - the version of the resource, in X.Y.Z-SOMETHING format a la Maven.
        cacheRoot - the path to the root of the cache.
        Returns:
        The db configuration to access the DB in read-only mode.
        Throws:
        eu.kidf.diversicon.core.exceptions.DivIoException - if fetch could not be performed
        Since:
        0.1.0

      • readData

        public static ExtractedStream readData(DivConfig divConfig,
                       String dataUrl,
                       boolean decompress)
        Gets input stream from a url pointing to possibly compressed data.
        Parameters:
        dataUrl - can be like:
        • classpath:/my/package/name/data.zip
        • file:/my/path/data.zip
        • http://...
        • jar:file:///home/user/data.jar!/my-file.txt
        • jar:file:///home/user/data.jar!/my-file.txt.zip
        • whatever protocol..
        decompress - if true and data is actually compressed in one of SUPPORTED_COMPRESSION_FORMATS returns the uncompressed stream (note no check is done to verify the archive contains only one file). In all other cases data stream is returned verbatim.
        divConfig - Configuration for accessing external resources. If unknown use DivConfig.of()
        Throws:
        eu.kidf.diversicon.core.exceptions.DivIoException - on error.
        Since:
        0.1.0
